org.opends.guitools.controlpanel.datamodel

Class IndexTableModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.table.AbstractTableModel
      • org.opends.guitools.controlpanel.datamodel.SortableTableModel
        • org.opends.guitools.controlpanel.datamodel.AbstractIndexTableModel
          • org.opends.guitools.controlpanel.datamodel.IndexTableModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparator<AbstractIndexDescriptor>, TableModel

    public class IndexTableModel
extends AbstractIndexTableModel
    The table model for the indexes. This is the table model used by the table that appears on the right side of the Manage Index dialog when the user clicks on the node "Index" and it gives a global view of the indexes defined on a given backend.

      • compare

        public int compare(AbstractIndexDescriptor index1,
                   AbstractIndexDescriptor index2)
        Comparable implementation.
        Parameters:
        index1 - the first index descriptor to compare.
        index2 - the second index descriptor to compare.
        Returns:
        1 if according to the sorting options set by the user the first index descriptor must be put before the second descriptor, 0 if they are equivalent in terms of sorting and -1 if the second descriptor must be put before the first descriptor.
